A legal practitioner, Henry Olisa Ogbogu, has congratulated the Governor of Anambra State, Prof Charles Chukwuma Soludo on his successful inauguration while commending his vision and determination to reposition and transform Anambra State for greatness. Ogbogu, Secretary, Soludo Support Group, FCT Chapter, in a press statement made available to journalists in Warri, Delta State on Sunday commended Soludo for heeding the calls of Anambra people to govern the state, and to put things right again to better their lives. He stated, “Anambra State called and you heeded the clarion call. The call to serve, the call to transform Anambra State and Ndi Anambra, the call to put Anambra State in her pride of place”. According to the lawyer, “Soludo’s election and subsequent inauguration mark the journey to greatness for Anambra State”. He expressed the hope that Soludo would excel beyond imagination while Anambra would be better for this choice.
He then appealed to the people of Anambra State to cooperate with and collectively support the new administration of Governor Soludo to make Anambra state better. Ogbogu also appreciated Governor Soludo for his appointment of Mr. Chinedu Nwoye as the Deputy Chief of Staff and Chief Protocol officer, describing the appointment as well deserved. He congratulated Nwoye on his appointment noting that it is a validation and testament to Nwoye’s hard work. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com